args: Phew! No sign of intemperate \nmischief-making found...FOR NOW.
Halloween is no excuse for excessive\ntomfoolishness and prankery.
It is a preacher's job to patrol her flock\nand ensure no one gets up to mischi—
Oh no! Are you all right, Estelle?
What is the meaning of this sudden and\ncompletely unprovoked assault from\nbehind my very person?!
Er, well, that's the... Um... Right, then.\nMy sincerest apologies. I didn't think it\nwould startle you quite so badly.
I know I was the one who said ＂trick or\ntreat,＂ but here—have some candy to\nmake up for the unintentional terror.
Ah, lovely. Thank you. ...Hmm. I'm only\nnow calming down enough to see that\nyou are dressed up for the occasion.
You like it? The others thought I needed\nto join in, so they made it for me.
You should do the same, Estelle.\nI mean, surely you can afford to cut loose\na LITTLE bit on Halloween, right?
Coming! ...Well, I'm off, Estelle.\nHave a fun Halloween!
A ＂fun Halloween,＂ is it?\nIf I could but spend it with him...
Ugh, what foolishness! I must put aside\nsuch thoughts and return to my patrol.
There will be nothing fun about a\nHalloween where a foolish prank leads\nto someone getting hur—
Eeeeeee hee hee! Looking to enjoy\nHalloween to the fullest, mmmm?
Aaaah ha ha ha! You got tricked HARD!\nOh my gosh, your face! YOUR FACE!
Bzzzt! Wrong. But forget about me, lady.\nLet's get to the real dirt here: You wanna\nspend Halloween with princey there.
Eeeee hee hee! Want me to teach you the\nREAL trick to enjoying this day?
As in pranks? Absolutely not!\nI am a woman of the cloth.
What sort of example would I be setting\nfor the children if I behaved like some...\nsome hooligan!
I don't care WHAT day it is! Mischief is\nmischief, and I won't hear another word!
But you're meant to prank on Halloween,\nwhich means NOT playing them is\nmisbehaving!
I've never heard a more ridiculous claim.
Think about it. Princey there is a pretty\nnice guy, yeah? So why would he go and\nscare the bejabbers outta ya?
It's because he KNOWS that not playing\ntricks on Halloween is misbehaving.\nThat's just the law, lady.
Look. You're a preacher and junk, yeah?\nSo what lesson are you teaching the\nkiddos by misbehaving like this?

Today's the one day meant for pranking,
so make the most of it! Do something new!
He told you to have fun, right? I mean,
it was practically a royal ORDER!
(Did the prince startle me so he might\ncorrect my misunderstanding of this\nstrange holiday?)
As a preacher, I do not relish the idea of\nmaking mischief, but I seem to have no\nchoice in the matter.
If playing tricks is upstanding behavior\non Halloween, I must obey!
...But why must I prank HIM, of all people?
He's the one you want to spend the day\nwith, isn't he?
That's how you know he's the perfect guy\nto prank. Now get out there and trick your\nlittle heart out!
Wait! ...Ugh. What in the world\nWAS that accursed thing?
Well, I suppose the prince DID startle me;\nit is only fair to return the favor.
Very well! Time to prank the prince!\nI'll call this one...Operation Stickyhands:\nThe Gluey Handshake Surprise!
Ha ha! Oh, but this brings me back.\nI used to do this to the head of my\nconvent, poor woman.
She'd have to walk us both to the bath\nhand-in-hand to scrub our fingers free!\nHmm? Hold a moment. That means...
BLARGH! You glued our hands together!
I wouldn't want to try to pry it loose by\nforce for fear of hurting you. We'll simply\nhave to walk hand-in-hand to the bath.
...Oh dear. I would die on the spot. I feel\nan overpowering need to wash my hands\nat the moment, in fact.
Let us stick to something simple, such as\nsneaking up behind him and covering his\neyes. That requires only minimal contact!
(Oh, but what if he's so startled he loses\nhis balance and...)
Ha ha ha! So it was you. Oh, you got\nme good indeed with that one, Estelle.
But I'm afraid you have me pinned here.\nWould you mind getting off?
N-no, I mustn't! I might accidentally injure\nhim! Yes, injuries. Must avoid injuries.

Then let us go simpler still: I walk up
behind him and give him a fright!
That will require only my voice,
not physical contact.
Ah, there he is. Now to just...
(Gah, I'm so nervous! What if it fails?!\nWhat if he isn't startled?!)
Are you gonna sit around and fret all day,\nor are you gonna trick someone?!
I-I'm going! Right now! It's just, er...\nMy legs don't wish to cooperate.
Oh, for the love of... Fine! I'll handle it.\nWatch and learn, sister.
You'll handle...? EEEEP! N-no!\nSomething is pushing me!
{player_name}! Th-this isn't...\nI wasn't pranking! It was...
Wait. Did you just play a Halloween\nprank on me, Estelle?
Er, I was just... I mean... Yes.\n...Did I get you?
Oh, you scared me good! But honestly,\nthe most surprising part is seeing you\ntake part in a trick.
Well, I wouldn't want to break\nany Halloween laws.
All you've done since the party began\nis walk around on patrol looking for\ntroublemakers and...so on.
I was hoping you'd enjoy some Halloween\nfun for yourself, and you did!
(So THAT'S why he shouted trick or treat\nat me! He was worried I wasn't enjoying\nmyself enough...)
I'm sorry, Estelle. Have I done\nsomething to offend you?
NO! No, not at all. But I hope you know\nwhat you're getting by telling me to\nindulge in all this.
Trick or treat. ...Now hand over the candy\nbefore I prank you again!
